The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Somdev trains with Roddick
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Somdev trains with Roddick
            OUR CORRESPONDENT            Somdev Dev Varman                           
	Mumbai: Somdev Dev Varmans career got a major boost this week when he got the chance to train with American world No. 8 Andy Roddick.         
	Dev Varman, Indias highest-ranked player at 205, has been working with Roddick, the since Monday in Austin, Texas.         
	To work with a top-10 player in the off-season is a dream opportunity for the 23-year-old.         
	The Tripura-born lad will be tutored by Roddicks coach Larry Stefanki during the 10-day programme, a statement from the players management said.         
	I am very excited at the oppurtunity to train with Andy under the watchful eye of Larry Stefanki. It will be a great learning curve for me, , Dev Varman said.         
	Stefanki has coached greats like John McEnroe, Marcelo Rios, Yevgeny Kafelnikov and, more recently, Fernando Gonzales.         
	Dev Varman, who will be staying at Roddicks house during the stint, will also benefit from working with the latters fitness trainer Doug Preen.                                                                                                                          
